solution: class Solution {
public:
    bool reorderedPowerOf2(int n) {
        string s = to_string(n);
        sort(s.begin(), s.end());
        for (int p = 0; p < 30; ++p) {
            string t = to_string(1 << p);
            sort(t.begin(), t.end());
            if (t == s) return true;
        }
        return false;
    }
};
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log n * log log n)
space complexity: O(log n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Pre-compute the digit multiset of every 2^p (0 ≤ p < 30) once, then compare the multiset of n (obtained by sorting its digits) against each. Sorting the digits of n and each 2^p dominates the cost; the number of digits is at most 10, so the constant factor is tiny.

